Library Management System

This is a Library Management System project built using Node.js, Express, and MongoDB. The system allows users to manage books and authors, including creating, reading, updating, and deleting (CRUD) operations.


Prerequisites
Node.js installed on your system
MongoDB installed on your system or a MongoDB Atlas cluster
Installation
Clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/Yash3440/git
Install dependencies: npm install


const MongoClient = require('mongodb').MongoClient;

const url = 'mongodb+srv://connectyash:yash3440@cluster1.lzkwo.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=Cluster1';


Start the server: node server.js
Open a web browser and navigate to http://localhost:5000
Features
Manage books: create, read, update, and delete books
Manage authors: create, read, update, and delete authors
Display book and author information
Folder Structure
client: client-side code (HTML, CSS, JavaScript)
server: server-side code (Node.js, Express)
models: database models (MongoDB)
routes: API routes (Express)
database: database connection and configuration
public: public assets (images, CSS, JavaScript files)
